{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0159T8GXigZy1hoif8jsNbeZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the context I need. From the handoff summaries, I know:\n\n1. `internal/` contains two composite sub-packages:\n   - `iam/` — a single http.Handler composing `lifecycle` (user CRUD + session tokens) and `authz` (RBAC) sub-packages, bound to :8082\n   - `metrics/` — a single http.Handler composing an in-memory event store and HTTP dispatch layer, bound to :8081\n\n2. The `internal/` level itself has a stub `README.md` that needs to be replaced.\n\n\n3. The `iam` package exposes lifecycle routes for user management and login/logout, plus authz routes for role-based access control, with the client passing user IDs between them via HTTP.\n4. The `metrics` package runs an in-memory event store with POST and GET endpoints for event handling.\n5. The `cmd` binary wires together both the metrics service on :8081 and the iam service on :8082.\n\nNow I need to create documentation for the `internal/` directory—a README that indexes the components with links to their individual docs, plus a data-flow document showing how iam and metrics interact. Let me check what's already in the output directory.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":338,"cache_read_input_tokens":20664,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":338},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8fd4abb-9741-42c2-ae4d-051524187dfc","uuid":"448b665d-5b80-4f7b-b4a5-7a80ceaf32a2"}
