{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KQEd2XEpJX4fLc4tovu4MC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I need to write two files:\n1. `README.md` — replace the placeholder with a proper directory index\n2. `data-flow.md` — cross-component data flow\n\nFrom the handoff summaries:\n\n**iam** (port :8082):\n- Composite: `lifecycle/` (user CRUD + session tokens) + `authz/` (RBAC) + `iam.go` (wiring)\n- Routes on :8082: lifecycle user/login/logout routes + authz roles/assignments/permissions routes\n\n\n- Client passes lifecycle user IDs to authz via HTTP\n\n**metrics** (port :8081):\n- Composite: `handlers/` (HTTP layer) + `store/` (in-memory storage) + `metrics.go` (wiring)  \n- Routes on :8081: POST /events, GET /events\n- In-memory event store with event-type allowlist\n\nThe two services are independent HTTP handlers wired onto separate ports by `cmd/platform`. For the data-flow doc, I need to map how the client interacts with each service and how they're orchestrated at the platform level.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":136,"cache_read_input_tokens":21558,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":136},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8fd4abb-9741-42c2-ae4d-051524187dfc","uuid":"3edf217a-013b-49a0-9ce7-7a050b4f3841"}
